text: I had the masala dosa($3) for breakfast. It was tasty and crispy, and the portion of potato was decent. Chutney and dhal were quite good as well. Overall, it was a good meal.

Do yourself, your stomach, your mouth and your wallet a favour - Skip this place entirely.
- thosai super oily.
- no tomato chutney
- no coconut chutney
- extremely bland or flavourless sambar dhal
- and serves fish curry with thosai? That's a profanity to south Indian cuisine:(

Dodgy eatery. No price menu. Have to ask every time you order.
Bought the Prata before. So so only. Flour tends to be undercooked.

Edible dosai. One ( looks/acts like the owner) of the Indians working there was extremely hostile and arrogant . He acted like as tho I am getting free food from him or trying to steal from him. What a mean person. Terrible experience.
The roti parata is not oily and good to eat when hot. Come with different curry but spicy and hot. Outside the coffee shop still under renovation but well covered up.
